parsedComplaintsResult.issueCategory: Fuel Hose Failure and Fuel Leak
parsedComplaintsResult.impact: A fuel hose failure can cause a fuel leak, which can lead to a vehicle fire, potentially resulting in serious injury or death.
symptoms: Fuel smell or odor
fuel leak
vehicle jerk or stall
engine hesitation
vehicle fire.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the center air flow duct can cause it to break away and crash down on the rear seats, potentially causing injury or distraction to occupants.
symptoms: The plastic material of the center air flow duct cracks
the duct deteriorates
the air duct housing is in danger of breaking away
the air conditioner vent fails
and falls on the driver's head.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The collapse of the camper bed can cause injury or discomfort to occupants.
symptoms: The bed collapses when getting down from it
the camper pops up out of its ledge.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The failure of the shoulder belt buckle attachments in the last row of seats can cause the belt to become stuck, preventing the occupant from exiting the vehicle freely, which can lead to entrapment and potentially serious injury or even death in emergency situations.
symptoms: The shoulder belt buckle attachment fails to release
the belt becomes stuck
the occupant is unable to exit the vehicle freely
the belt is difficult to release.

parsedComplaintsResult.impact: The sudden engine stall and subsequent fire can cause a loss of vehicle control, accidents, and potentially lead to serious injuries or fatalities.
symptoms: The engine stops running while driving
the vehicle stalls
smoke emerges from the rear of the vehicle
flames appear from the back of the vehicle
the vehicle catches fire.
